name: Kek
description: Kek is more than just a meme — he is rooted in ancient mythology. In Egyptian legend, Kek was the primordial god of chaos and darkness, often shown with the head of a frog. He ruled the space between night and day, symbolizing transformation, rebirth, and unseen forces shaping reality. Centuries later, Kek was reborn on the internet as the God of Memes, a symbol of viral chaos, inside jokes, and “meme magic.” The frog became his face, and his power became the unpredictable energy that drives culture online. Today, Kek lives on as $KEK, a memecoin powered not only by speculation but also by belief, community, and the magic of memes.
